-2011\n|33\n|2,390,000,000 AUD.\n|\n|-\n|[[Cyclone Yasi]]\n|2011\n|1\n|3,600,000,000 USD (2011).\n|\n|-\n|[[2013 Tasmanian bushfires|Tasmanian bushfires]]\n|2013\n|1\n|170+ buildings.\n|\n|-\n|[[2013 New South Wales bushfires|New South Wales bushfires]]\n|2013\n|1\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Cyclone Oswald]]\n|2013\n|7\n|2,520,000,000 USD (2013).\n|\n|-\n|[[2014 Brisbane hailstorm|Brisbane hailstorm]]\n|2014\n|0\n|1,100,000,000 AUD.\n|\n|-\n|[[Cyclone Ita]]\n|2014\n|0\n|1,150,000,000 USD (2014).\n|\n|-\n|[[2015 Sampson Flat bushfires|Sampson Flat bushfires]]\n|2015\n|0\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[2015 Esperance bushfires|Esperance bushfires]]\n|2015\n|4\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[2015 Pinery bushfire|Pinery bushfire]]\n|2015\n|2\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[2017 Carwoola bushfire|Carwoola bushfire]]\n|2017\n|0\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Cyclone Debbie]]\n|2017\n|14\n|2,730,000,000 USD (2017).\n|\n|-\n|[[2018 Tathra bushfire|Tathra bushfire]]\n|2018\n|0\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[2019-2020 Australian bushfire season]]\n|2019-2020\n|34{{efn|At least 34 (As of 24 Jan 2020)}}\n|5,900+ buildings\n|\n|}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of natural disasters in New Zealand]]\n* [[List of largest fires of the 21st-century]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Natural disasters in Australia]]\n[[Category:Lists of disasters in Australia]]\n[[Category:Lists of natural disasters]]\n[[Category:Disasters in Australia]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\nThis is a '''list all major of natural disasters in Australian history.''' The [[Natural disaster|natural disasters]] included here are all the events which resulted in significant loss of life or property due to natural, non-biological processes  of the [[Earth]] within [[Australia|Australian]] territory.  \n{{Incomplete list|date=December 2019}}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+\n!Event\n!Year\n!Death toll\n!Material destruction\n!Notes\n|-\n|[[Black Thursday bushfires]]\n|1851\n|12\n|One million sheep and thousands of cattle\n|\n|-\n|[[Red Tues