01506/https://knowledge.aidr.org.au/resources/bushfire-new-south-wales-1974/ |archivedate=13 January 2020 |quote=Approximately 15 per cent of Australia's physical land mass sustained extensive fire damage. This equates to roughly around 117 million ha. |url-status=live }}</ref>\n|-\n|[[1974 Brisbane flood|Brisbane flood]]\n|1974\n|16\n|980,000,000 AUD.\n|\n|-\n|[[Cyclone Tracy]]\n|1974\n|71\n|645,350,000 USD (1974)\n|\n|-\n|[[Cyclone Alby]]\n|1978\n|7\n|45,000,000 USD (1978).\n|\n|-\n|[[Ash Wednesday bushfires]]\n|1983\n|75\n|2,400 houses.\n|\n|-\n|[[Cyclone Orson]]\n|1989\n|5\n|16,800,000 USD (1989).\n|\n|-\n|[[1989 Newcastle earthquake|Newcastle earthquake]]\n|1989\n|13\n|4,000,000,000 AUD.\n|\n|-\n|[[1994 Eastern seaboard fires|Eastern seaboard fires]]\n|1993-1994\n|4\n|225 homes.\n|\n|-\n|[[Gracetown landslide]]\n|1996\n|9\n|\n|About 30 tonnes of rock and sand fell from a cliff to below spectators of a school surf event.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://knowledge.aidr.org.au/resources/landslide-gracetown-western-australia/|title=Landslide - Gracetown, Western Australia {{!}} Australian Disaster Resilience Knowledge Hub|website=knowledge.aidr.org.au|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[1997 Thredbo landslide|Thredbo landslide]]\n|1997\n|18\n|\n|One victim was found alive after 60 hours of being buried.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://knowledge.aidr.org.au/resources/landslide-thredbo-1997/|title=Landslide - Thredbo, 1997 {{!}} Australian Disaster Resilience Knowledge Hub|website=knowledge.aidr.org.au|access-date=2019-12-30}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Linton Bushfire]]\n|1998\n|5\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[1998 Sydney to Hobart Yacht Race|Sydney to Hobart Yacht Race]]\n|1998\n|6\n|30,000,000 AUD.\n|A [[supercell]] storm caused chaos during the annual [[Sydney to Hobart Yacht Race]], with only 44 out of 115 yachts finishing.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://knowledge.aidr.org.au/resources/maritimecoastal-sydney-to-hobart-yacht-race-1998/|title=Maritime/Coastal - Sydney to Hobart Yacht race, 1998 {{!}} Aus